\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{Y}$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $E(Y)=E(\hat{Y})=0$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\MSE(\alpha+\beta\hat{Y}) & = & \beta^{2}\Var(\hat{Y})-2\beta\Cov(\hat{Y},Y)+\Var Y^{2}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Differentiate with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 and set equal to zero, so that 
\begin_inset Formula $2\beta\Var(\hat{Y})-2\Cov(\hat{Y},Y)=0$
\end_inset

.
